I think Fortean phenomena like street light interference are very important because they serve as undeniable proof that the technology and society producing them contains an organic element that makes the entirety of life coherent in some way.

If for example we have a light bulb that does not blink at the apparition of a ghost or a street lamp that does not turn off when a person with a predisposition towards the other world passes under it, it means all that is organic has been hollowed out of our physical environment

When I was like 6 years old I had a big Winnie the Pooh poster over my bed with all of the characters hugging Eeyore together and my dad said when he had to wake up 6 AM to go to work looking at it made him feel warm and cheered him up when he felt too tired. Will always love him

Putting a character like this in a children's cartoon was a very enlightened move. Some people just have a melancholic personality and are naturally prone to being always sad. You might befriend one or be one of them yourself. It is what it is. They need to have good friends too.
